        {
          "widget": {
            "name": "6deac568",
            "multilineTextboxSpec": {
              "lines": [
                "## What we found\n",
                "\n",
                "**Late delivery costs 2.6 review points.** Orders arriving 10+ days late<br>average 1.7 stars versus 4.3 for early deliveries. 6.8% of delivered orders<br>miss their promised date.\n",
                "\n",
                "**Lateness is seasonal, not chronic.** The baseline sits near 3-4%, but<br>demand peaks drive spikes above 19% — the problem is capacity, not process.\n",
                "\n",
                "**Geography drives delivery time.** Remote states average materially longer<br>delivery windows than the southeast corridor, and freight costs follow.\n",
                "\n",
                "## Recommended actions\n",
                "\n",
                "1. Set seller-specific promise dates rather than a single national estimate\n",
                "2. Add carrier capacity ahead of known demand peaks\n",
                "3. Review the bottom sellers by on-time rate, weighted by revenue exposure"
              ]
            }
          },
          "position": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 15,
            "width": 12,
            "height": 6
          }
        },
